VALUES
(44, 9, 18, 44, 2, 38, 38, 'and was baptized', 'Baptism and Spiritual Renewal', 'This connection highlights the theme of baptism as a means of spiritual renewal. In both passages, baptism is presented as a crucial step following a transformative experience, emphasizing its role in receiving sight and the Holy Spirit.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 18, 44, 13, 12, 13, 'received sight forthwith', 'Transformation and Belief', 'This connection highlights the theme of transformation leading to belief. In Acts 9:18, the physical restoration of sight symbolizes spiritual awakening, which parallels the deputy''s astonishment and belief in Acts 13:12-13.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 18, 44, 13, 37, 38, 'received sight forthwith', 'Connection of Sight and Forgiveness', 'This connection highlights the theme of transformation and renewal. In Acts 9:18, the restoration of sight symbolizes spiritual awakening, while Acts 13:37-38 emphasizes the forgiveness of sins through Christ, suggesting a deeper spiritual insight gained through faith.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 18, 47, 4, 6, 6, 'received sight forthwith', 'Light and Revelation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of illumination and transformation. In Acts, the scales falling from Saul''s eyes symbolizes a newfound clarity, while in 2 Corinthians, God shining light in hearts signifies spiritual enlightenment.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 19, 44, 26, 20, 20, 'certain days with the disciples which were at Damascus', 'Connection of Repentance and Strengthening', 'This connection highlights Saul''s initial strengthening in Damascus and his subsequent mission to preach repentance there. Both passages emphasize the significance of Damascus as a starting point for Saul''s ministry and the call to turn to God.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 19, 9, 30, 12, 12, 'was strengthened', 'Strengthening Through Food', 'Both passages emphasize the restoration of strength through food. In Acts, Saul is strengthened after eating, while in 1 Samuel, the man regains his spirit after consuming figs and raisins.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 19, 48, 1, 17, 17, 'with the disciples which were at Damascus', 'Saul''s Time in Damascus', 'Both passages emphasize Saul''s presence in Damascus after his conversion. Acts 9:19 mentions his time with the disciples there, while Galatians 1:17 indicates his return to Damascus after going to Arabia.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 19, 21, 9, 7, 7, 'received meat, he was strengthened', 'Joy in Strength and Provision', 'This connection highlights the theme of nourishment and joy in both passages. In Acts, Saul is strengthened after receiving food, while Ecclesiastes encourages enjoying bread and wine with a merry heart, suggesting that physical sustenance is linked to spiritual well-being.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 19, 44, 11, 26, 26, 'was strengthened', 'Saul''s Growth and Teaching', 'This connection highlights Saul''s early strengthening and subsequent teaching role. Both passages emphasize the development of Saul into a key figure in the early church.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 19, 9, 10, 10, 12, 'Saul certain days with the disciples', 'Transformation of Saul', 'This connection highlights the transformation of Saul in both passages. In Acts, Saul is strengthened and begins to associate with disciples, while in 1 Samuel, he is empowered by the Spirit and prophesies among prophets, indicating a significant change in identity.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 20, 43, 20, 28, 28, 'that he is the Son of God', 'Recognition of Christ''s Divinity', 'This connection highlights the acknowledgment of Jesus as divine. In Acts, Jesus is proclaimed as ''the Son of God,'' while in John, Thomas recognizes Him as ''My Lord and my God.'' Both passages emphasize the identity of Jesus in relation to God.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 20, 48, 1, 23, 24, NULL, 'Transformation of Saul to Paul', 'This connection highlights Saul''s dramatic shift from persecutor to preacher. Both passages emphasize his new role in proclaiming Christ as the Son of God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 20, 48, 2, 20, 20, 'that he is the Son of God', 'Connection of Christ''s Identity', 'This connection highlights the identity of Christ as the Son of God in both passages. Acts emphasizes preaching Christ as the Son of God, while Galatians speaks of living by faith in the Son of God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 20, 62, 4, 14, 15, 'that he is the Son of God', 'Confession of Jesus as Son', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of Jesus as the Son of God. Acts 9:20 highlights preaching Christ as the Son, while 1 John 4:15 speaks of confessing Jesus as the Son of God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 20, 19, 2, 7, 7, 'Son of God', 'Connection of Sonship in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus as the Son of God. Acts 9:20 proclaims Jesus'' identity, while Psalms 2:7 declares God''s affirmation of His Sonship.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 20, 40, 4, 3, 3, 'he is the Son of God', 'Connection of Sonship', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of Jesus as the Son of God. In Acts, Saul preaches this truth, while in Matthew, the tempter challenges Jesus'' identity as the Son of God.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 20, 40, 26, 63, 66, 'that he is the Son of God', 'Connection of Christ''s Identity', 'This connection highlights the affirmation of Jesus as the ''Son of God'' in both passages. In Acts, Saul preaches this identity, while in Matthew, the high priest directly questions Jesus about being the ''Son of God.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 21, 44, 8, 3, 3, 'destroyed them which called on this name', 'Saul''s Persecution of the Church', 'Both passages emphasize Saul''s actions against believers. Acts 9:21 refers to Saul''s intent to bind those who called on the name of Jesus, while Acts 8:3 describes his earlier persecution of the church, highlighting his transformation.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 21, 44, 9, 13, 14, NULL, 'Connection of Saul''s Actions', 'Both passages emphasize the evil Saul has done to those who call on the name of the Lord. They highlight the fear and amazement surrounding his transformation from persecutor to believer.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 21, 53, 1, 10, 10, 'Is not this he that destroyed them', 'Transformation and Belief', 'This connection highlights the theme of transformation and belief in both passages. Acts 9:21 speaks to the amazement of those who recognized the change in Saul, while 2 Thessalonians 1:10 emphasizes the importance of belief in the testimony of the saints.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 21, 40, 13, 54, 55, 'were amazed', 'Astonishment at Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of astonishment in both passages. In Acts, the people are amazed at Saul''s transformation, while in Matthew, the crowd is astonished by Jesus'' wisdom and works.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 21, 48, 1, 13, 24, NULL, 'Transformation of Paul', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s past as a persecutor of the church and his subsequent transformation into a preacher of the faith. The amazement expressed in Acts 9:21 aligns with Galatians 1:23, where the churches recognize the drastic change in his role.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 21, 19, 71, 7, 7, NULL, 'Wonder and Refuge Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of being a ''wonder'' in the eyes of others. In Acts, the amazement at Saul''s transformation parallels the psalmist''s experience of being a ''wonder unto many,'' while both affirm reliance on God as a refuge.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 21, 23, 8, 18, 18, NULL, 'Signs and Wonders Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of being a sign or wonder. In Acts, the amazement of the people reflects the transformative power of faith, similar to how Isaiah speaks of signs and wonders in Israel.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 22, 44, 18, 5, 5, 'this is very Christ', 'Proclamation of Jesus as Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the proclamation of Jesus as the Christ. In Acts 9:22, Saul confounds the Jews by proving Jesus is the Christ, while in Acts 18:5, Paul testifies to the Jews that Jesus was Christ.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 22, 23, 40, 29, 29, NULL, 'Strength and Empowerment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of strength being given to those who are weak. In Acts, Saul''s increased strength confounds others, while Isaiah speaks of God giving power to the faint.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 22, 42, 21, 15, 15, 'confounded the Jews', 'Connection of Divine Wisdom', 'Both passages emphasize the ability to confound adversaries through wisdom and strength. Saul''s ability to ''confound the Jews'' aligns with the promise of wisdom given in Luke.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 22, 44, 18, 27, 28, 'proving that this is very Christ', 'Connection of Convincing the Jews', 'Both passages emphasize the act of convincing the Jews about Jesus being the Christ. Saul in Acts 9:22 and the unnamed individual in Acts 18:28 both demonstrate strength in their arguments, proving Jesus'' identity through scripture.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 22, 46, 1, 27, 27, 'confounded the Jews', 'Confounding the Wise and Strong', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of confounding those who are wise and strong. Saul''s ability to confound the Jews in Damascus parallels God''s choice of foolish and weak things to confound the mighty.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 22, 18, 17, 9, 9, NULL, 'Strength in Righteousness', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of increasing strength. In Acts, Saul''s strength grows as he proves Christ''s identity, while Job highlights the righteous becoming stronger in their way.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
